text: A post from a   year old about mental health and high school Hey everyone  I frequented here a while back but now I m  old  I guess I just wanted to say you hear so much BS about high school as a teen  you ll be told it s the best time of your life and they ll say they wish they could go back to when it was carefree and easy again  No consequences  new love  friends  etc It s all bullshit  All of it  High school can suck  bad  I ll forever look back at high school terribly  Depression  fake friends  bad family life  and more  The good news though  It s over pretty fast I actually dropped out and got my GED in my late Junior year because my mental health and school was so terrible I couldn t take it so I know what I m talking about  I felt hopeless and without any drive for a future  high school completely killed the kid who wanted to be an astrophysicist and read books every day   But now  I m a   year old full time artist and gamedev  I work on Minecraft content rn  I have a good girlfriend and two pets  and I feel better than ever  Is it perfect  Hell no  but life isn t  I still struggle  I still have anxiety disorder  I have money issues but HS is over Please  realize it does get better and it sure as hell isn t the best your life will be despite what you re told  HS sucks  but adult life sucks WAY less  Please keep strong  Stay safe everyone PS  and for the love of god realize that trade jobs  carpenter  roofer  plumber  etc  are   viable careers  don t require college  and can pay extremely well
